    <div class="project-overview-content">

        <h1>Project overview</h1>

        <h2 class="heading">What we had <span>to do</span></h2><!--Description of project-->
        <p>
            For this project I was in a team with two other people. We had to make a mobile application
            that was for storing collections of different items. We had to do research on similar 
            applications as well as design what our application would look likes as well as the basic flow. 
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading">What we <span>did</span></h2>
        <p>
            We used Figma to do the designs and to make the logo.
            We used Android Studio as our IDE and we used Java as the programming language.
            We also stored all the data on a database and we used Firebase for that.
            We then had to present our application using our phones.
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading">Potential problems and <span>errors</span></h2>
        <p>
            These are a few problems that might occur:
            <ol style="font-size:1.4rem; margin-right:20px;">
                <li>You will need android studio to view the code easily and to run the project.</li>
                <li>The database might have been deactivated but maybe not</li>
            </ol>

        </p>

    </div>

</section>




